==Trivia== *In the game "Super Mario Galaxy 3: Arrival of the Dark King" a [[Luma]] in a hidden area referred to God Mario by saying "You would surely could do a lot in your ''Ultimate Form." '' A reference to God Mario. *There are two forms that grants Mario golden stature and sparks. The other form is [[Golden Mario|Gold Mario.]] It allows Mario to throw golden fireballs that could turn brick blocks and enemies into golden coins. But instead of a golden aura, Gold Mario is made entirely out of golden energy. *Though not told in its starring game, God Mario is said to be potentially omnipotent and is the most powerful thing in the entire Nintendoverse, even maybe the video game universe. It is said in the trophy gallery of Super Smash Bros. Brawl 2. *In the trophy gallery it also said "...With Mario possessing infinite power." Another statement to show God Mario's omnipotence. *The trophy of God Mario is the rarest trophy that could be obtained in Super Smash Bros. Brawl 2. The only way to obtain it is to beat the "Boss Battles" mode in insane difficulty with only one stock. After that, a challenger appears, being Dark Mario. When you beat them all, you will be rewarded with the trophy and Dark Mario will become a playable character. *[[God Waluigi]] is irrelivant, that is because God Mario is created first. And the game specifically said that it was God Mario who created the multiverse. [[Category:Mario's Power-Ups]] [[Category:OCs]] [[Category:Recolors]] [[Category:Mario]] [[Category:Mario's Brothers]] [[Category:Mario Series]] [[Category:Forms]] [[Category:Power-Ups]] [[Category:Powerups]]

